<subSubSection pageId="123" pageNumber="124" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="123" pageNumber="124">
East Africa, coastal sand, coral outcrops and grassland near the sea: Tanzania (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Tanner</emphasis>
2211); Kenya (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Irwin</emphasis>
271, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Greenway</emphasis>
10454); Somalia (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Terry</emphasis>
3466);?Mozambique (
<bibRefCitation author="Verdcourt, B" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="213" pageNumber="214" pagination="459 - 464" publicationUrl="10.2307/4110047" refId="B375" refString="Verdcourt, B, 1982. Corrections and additions to the &quot;Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V. Kew Bulletin 37: 459 - 464, DOI: 10.2307/4110047" title="Corrections and additions to the &quot; Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V." url="10.2307/4110047" volume="37" year="1982">Verdcourt 1982</bibRefCitation>
: 483).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="124" lastPageNumber="125" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="124" lastPageNumber="125" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">
This species is not so distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Franch., Sert. Somal. 41. 1882. (Franchet" authorityYear="1882" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus capituliferus" order="Solanales" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capituliferus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">
<pageBreakToken pageId="124" pageNumber="125" start="start">Convolvulus</pageBreakToken>
capituliferus
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differing principally in its perennial habit and long-pedunculate heads. Three collections (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Tanner</emphasis>
2338, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Hicks</emphasis>
808, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Kokwaro</emphasis>
15114) are intermediate having subsessile inflorescences combined with a clearly perennial habit. The first is from Mlangoni in Tanga Province in Tanzania while the last two are from the Tsavo National Park area (
<geoCoordinate degrees="3" direction="south" minutes="17" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="-3.2833333">3° 17'S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="38" direction="east" minutes="32" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="38.533333">38° 32' E</geoCoordinate>
), all in the interior behind coastal 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verdc., Kew Bull. 12: 344. 1957. (Verdcourt" authorityYear="1957" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus jefferyi" order="Solanales" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jefferyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Convolvulus jefferyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but some distance from any known station for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Franch., Sert. Somal. 41. 1882. (Franchet" authorityYear="1882" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus capituliferus" order="Solanales" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capituliferus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Convolvulus capituliferus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which grows in northern Kenya.
</paragraph>
